<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-21T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-21T11:00:00-05:00" n="352" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d352">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 Netherlands/60:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Emmet</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-21T12:00:00-04:00">May
                                        21, 1936—noon</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>9. Legation’s despatch No. 403 of April 18. Please submit immediate
                                telegraphic report on present status of Government’s proposed
                                legislation to prevent fraudulent exportation to the United States
                                of alcohol from the Netherlands. Do you perceive any objection to
                                our notifying Belgian Government that such legislation is
                                contemplated as a means of persuading the latter to do likewise?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>